                         R E A D   T H I S !
                       

        This is a compendium of Songs, Poetry, and other Stuff that I 
have picked up over 22 or so years membership in the Society for 
Creative Anachronism, Inc. 
        This collection is NOT FOR SALE! It is FREE! It is made 
available for fair use within the SCA Inc. only, and must not be sold 
in any form. 

HOWEVER: There are copyrighted songs and poems in here. I have
made every effort to credit authors, where known, and to give the 
appropriate copyright information. If an entry is marked by an 
author's name, but no copyright information accompanies it, then 
ASSUME IT IS COPYRIGHTED TO THAT AUTHOR AND DO NOT PERFORM IT FOR 
PROFIT! 
        My own songs are free for performance, within the SCA, so long 
as credit is given. If you wish to record them........ contact CHRIS
MASTERS PRODUCTIONS (602) 971-0114. Please credit your source, on the 
others. 
        I wish I could credit everyone from whom I got some of these...
Trude Lacklandia, Caradoc ap Cador, Gwyddion, Stephen of the Grove, Janos
Throngcleaver, Bertram of Bearington, Thorfinn Halfblind, Giles "Funny
Hats" Hill of Sweetwater, Yang the (very) Nauseating, Ciorstan ....and
all the rest of the many creative crazies in the SCA. THANKS!
        This is NOT a complete selection of my own songs and poems, 
because some of them were written in the heat of anger, and thus are 
not suitable for publication! Don't ask! (even mundanely!) What you 
see is what you get! This collection may be copied and passed on to 
SCA and related groups. This file MUST be included. 

        Enjoy!

        NOTE: Pagination is by area, due to the constraints of using
electronic media, and not by the whole book. Page numbers have been
left blank for -my- convenience. The pages are formatted for 60 lines
per page.
        This collection may be file-requested thru any FIDO-net BBS
using the filenames BARD-1.ZIP, BARD-X.ZIP, and SCAPOEM.ZIP. Address 
the file-request to 1:114/29 DEUS EX MACHINA BBS, (602) 439-8070. The 
files are periodically updated and expanded, and any updates can be found
by file requesting 114-29.ARC.
        A collection of prose articles may be file-requested under the
filename BARDIC2.ARC, and a large collection of Irish/Scots songs may be
file-requested under the name CELTIC.ZIP.....

                         -Ioseph of Locksley
                          the Whyte Bard


